[This withdrawal of the garrisons to the Roman bank was in strict accor- dance with the policy of Augustus,⁴ and was, as sar as Lower Germany is concerned, permanent. Roman suzerainty was indeed still recognized by some of the tribes nearest the Rhine,⁸ and a strip of territory on the right bank was kept clear of Germans and reserved for the use of the Roman troops ‘ ; but that the order of Claudius-was carried out is proved by the absence os any later traces of military occupatiori beyond the Lower Rhine⁷ such as are found along the valley of the Main opposite Mainz.—P.]
